      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky. NORDIC INVADER (6) resumes and started his last campaign in good style, placing over 950m at this track. Has good numbers and is sure to make his presence felt. Stablemate RAFF VADER (7) resumes and is good enough if presented forward this time around. Went close in an Open 34 this track/trip two back, and a winning rider, Wiggins, is reunited. Will likely settle back and finish hard. BELLZEN (1) resumed improved by the new stable, finishing well to win this track/trip. Keeps the handy 2kg claim and won't have to improve much to be fighting out the finish. Ditto ACCEPT POWER (8), who posted a similar figure winning this track/trip first-up at big odds. Has the tongue tie on and responded. SHERE KHAN (4) is a leader who could make the finish forgiving the latest.",
